VALUES ('20% Spike In Mortgage Applications (US)', '20-spike-in-mortgage-applications', '<p id=""><strong id="">Mortgage demand just jumped 20% in a single week.</strong> That‚Äôs not just a number‚Äîit‚Äôs a signal.</p><p id="">Buyers are paying attention. A dip in rates has pulled more of them back into the market, and that momentum could mean more competition, stronger offers, and better opportunities for sellers.</p><p id="">Real estate moves in cycles, and smart buyers and sellers move with it. The key is knowing when to act.</p><p id="">Here‚Äôs what this shift means for your clients‚Äîand how you can help them stay ahead.</p>', 'https://ik.imagekit.io/listingleads/Campaigns/Email/20-spike-in-mortgage-applications/thumbnail-20-spike-in-mortgage-applications.png', '<p id="">Mortgage demand spikes 20%</p>', '<p id="">CNBC just reported a <strong id="">20% spike in mortgage applications</strong>‚Äîa massive shift in just one week.</p><p>‚Äç</p><p id="">So, what does this mean for you?</p><p>‚Äç</p><p id="">Two key takeaways:</p><ul id=""><li id=""><strong id="">Buyers are watching rates closely.</strong> A dip to <strong id="">6.73%</strong>‚Äîthe lowest since last year‚Äîhas pulled more buyers back into the market.</li><li id=""><strong id="">Sellers could see increased demand.</strong> More buyers re-entering means a greater chance for competitive offers and faster sales.</li></ul><p>‚Äç</p><p id="">As always, I‚Äôm here to help you navigate the market and make the most of these shifts.</p><p>‚Äç</p><p id="">Sincerely,</p><p id="">[Your Name]</p><p>‚Äç</p><p id="">P.S. If you‚Äôre considering whether now is the right time for you to buy or sell, just reply to this email and let‚Äôs chat. I‚Äôd love to give you some personalized guidance to help you make the best decision.</p>', NULL, 'Prospects', ARRAY['past-clients', 'soi', 'direct-response'], 'Prospects', NULL, 'https://ik.imagekit.io/listingleads/Campaigns/Email/20-spike-in-mortgage-applications/example-20-spike-in-mortgage-applications.png', '[{"title":"Copy Subject Line and Message to CRM","body":""},{"title":"Transferring Email Content to CRM","body":"<ol id=\"\"><li id=\"\">Copy Subject: Highlight and copy the <strong id=\"\">subject line</strong> from your email draft.</li><li id=\"\">Paste Subject: Open the email blast app and paste it into the <strong id=\"\">subject line</strong> field.</li><li id=\"\">Copy Email Content: Return to your draft, copy the <strong id=\"\">email content</strong>.</li><li id=\"\">Paste Content: Paste it in the <strong id=\"\">message body</strong> of the email blast app.</li><li id=\"\">Review and Send: Check for accuracy, then schedule or send the email.</li></ol><p>‚Äç</p>"}]', 'US', false, true);

