VALUES ('Client Success Story: Do you need to fix up your house before you sell?', 'do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell-client-success-story', '<p id="">Most sellers assume they need to spend thousands fixing up their home before they can sell. But here‚Äôs the truth: <em id="">They might not need to.</em></p><p id="">This email is so effective because it <em id="">challenges that assumption</em> with real results. If you recently worked with a client who had an outdated home, needed big-ticket repairs, and believed a traditional sale wasn‚Äôt worth the hassle, this is your chance to shift their perspective. Instead of pouring money into renovations or taking a lowball offer from an iBuyer, they leaned on your network of buyers. The result? A sale that netted them significantly more than an instant offer.</p><p id="">The key takeaway: Selling <em id="">as-is</em> isn‚Äôt a last resort‚Äîit‚Äôs a strategy. And when sellers have the right expert in their corner, they don‚Äôt have to choose between convenience and maximizing their profit.</p>', 'https://ik.imagekit.io/listingleads/Campaigns/Email/do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell-client-success-story/thumbnail-do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell-client-success-story.png', '<p>Do you need to fix up your house before you sell?</p>', '<p id="">68% of homeowners make at least one home improvement before listing their home.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id=""><em id="">But does it always pay off?</em></p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">Not everyone will agree with me on this, but‚Ä¶</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">You <em id="">don‚Äôt</em> need to sink thousands of dollars into your home before you sell it, and here‚Äôs why‚Äî</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">Buyer demand is <strong id="">still</strong> strong despite frustratingly high interest rates.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">Recently I worked with a client who owned their home for 23 years.</p><p id="">‚Äç<br><br>It needed a new roof, the appliances were out-of-date, the rugs had been there since the 90‚Äôs.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">Needless to say, it needed work.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">But I wasn‚Äôt worried.</p><p id="">‚Äç<br><br>Because I have a network of over 4,202 buyers, I knew I‚Äôd be able to find the right buyer who could overlook the cosmetic issues and was willing to pay a premium for it.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">So we brought the home to market and got it under contract for $42,000 <em id="">more than an iBuyer would‚Äôve paid for it.</em></p><p id=""><br>So the bottom-line is‚Äîbefore you start fixing up your home or settle for one of those ‚Äúinstant cash-offer‚Äù solutions, we should talk.&nbsp;</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">My cell is 555-555-5555.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">I look forward to hearing from you,</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">[Your Name]</p>', NULL, 'Entire Database', ARRAY['past-clients', 'soi', 'direct-response'], 'Everyone', NULL, 'https://ik.imagekit.io/listingleads/Campaigns/Email/do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell-client-success-story/example-do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell-client-success-story.png', '[{"title":"Copy Subject Line and Message to CRM","body":""},{"title":"Transferring Email Content to CRM","body":"<ol id=\"\"><li id=\"\">Copy Subject: Highlight and copy the <strong id=\"\">subject line</strong> from your email draft.</li><li id=\"\">Paste Subject: Open the email blast app and paste it into the <strong id=\"\">subject line</strong> field.</li><li id=\"\">Copy Email Content: Return to your draft, copy the <strong id=\"\">email content</strong>.</li><li id=\"\">Paste Content: Paste it in the <strong id=\"\">message body</strong> of the email blast app.</li><li id=\"\">Review and Send: Check for accuracy, then schedule or send the email.</li></ol><p>‚Äç</p>"}]', 'US', false, true);

