VALUES ('Do you need to fix up your house before you sell?', 'do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell', '<p id="">One of the biggest misconceptions sellers have? That listing with an agent means weeks of expensive repairs, dealing with contractors, and endless headaches. Companies like Opendoor have capitalized on that fear, selling the promise of certainty, convenience, and speed. And guess what? It‚Äôs worked‚Äîover 30,000 homes bought in just two years.</p><p id="">But here‚Äôs the truth: Many of these sellers are leaving <em id="">real money</em> on the table. They might not need to renovate to sell. They might just need access to the right buyer.</p><p id="">This email is so effective because it <em id="">challenges the seller‚Äôs assumptions</em>. Most believe they <em id="">have</em> to fix up their home to attract buyers, but is there a different story? Not every buyer is looking for perfect‚Äîmany prioritize location, potential, and value. And with your extensive network of buyers, you can connect sellers with the right match, without forcing them into costly renovations.</p><p id=""><strong id="">Pro tip:</strong> Strengthen this email by adding a local stat on buyer demand. Show sellers that homes‚Äîeven ones that need work‚Äîare still moving fast in your market. The more relevant the data, the more powerful your message.</p>', 'https://ik.imagekit.io/listingleads/Campaigns/Email/do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell/thumbnail-do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell.png', '<p>Do you need to fix up your house before you sell?</p>', '<p id="">68% of homeowners make at least one home improvement before listing their home.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id=""><em id="">But does it always pay off?</em></p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">Not everyone will agree with me on this, but‚Ä¶</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">You <em id="">don‚Äôt</em> need to sink thousands of dollars into your home before you sell it, and here‚Äôs why‚Äî</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">Buyer demand is <strong id="">still</strong> strong despite frustratingly high interest rates.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">In fact, homes in all conditions are selling (yes, really) because not every buyer is looking for ‚Äúperfect.‚Äù A lot of buyers are looking for potential, location, and value.</p><p>‚Äç</p><p id="">Because I have a network of over <strong id="">4,202 buyers</strong>, I know how to connect sellers with the right people‚Äîbuyers who see past cosmetic updates and are willing to pay for the real value of a home.</p><p>‚Äç</p><p id="">So if you have a home that needs the roof repaired, or the carpet ripped up, or the 90s wallpaper finally taken down‚Äîdon‚Äôt settle for one of those ‚Äúinstant cash offer‚Äù solutions.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">Instead, let‚Äôs have a conversation: 555-555-5555.</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">I look forward to hearing from you,</p><p id="">[Your Name]</p><p id="">‚Äç</p><p id="">P.S. You might be thinking, <em id="">"But you''re an agent, not a contractor. How do I know I can trust your advice?"</em> Fair question. My job isn‚Äôt to push renovations‚Äîit‚Äôs to help you <strong id="">net the most money possible.</strong> I‚Äôve worked with sellers in all kinds of situations, and I know what actually adds value (and what‚Äôs just a money pit). Before you commit to spending thousands, let‚Äôs talk through your options:<strong id=""> 555-555-5555</strong>.</p>', NULL, 'Entire Database', ARRAY['past-clients', 'soi', 'direct-response'], 'Everyone', NULL, 'https://ik.imagekit.io/listingleads/Campaigns/Email/do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell/example-do-you-need-to-fix-up-your-house-before-you-sell.png', '[{"title":"Copy Subject Line and Message to CRM","body":""},{"title":"Transferring Email Content to CRM","body":"<ol id=\"\"><li id=\"\">Copy Subject: Highlight and copy the <strong id=\"\">subject line</strong> from your email draft.</li><li id=\"\">Paste Subject: Open the email blast app and paste it into the <strong id=\"\">subject line</strong> field.</li><li id=\"\">Copy Email Content: Return to your draft, copy the <strong id=\"\">email content</strong>.</li><li id=\"\">Paste Content: Paste it in the <strong id=\"\">message body</strong> of the email blast app.</li><li id=\"\">Review and Send: Check for accuracy, then schedule or send the email.</li></ol><p>‚Äç</p>"}]', 'US', false, true);

